{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T06:51:25.386Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of calculating how the loss (error) changes with respect to every parameter (weight and bias) in a neural network. This is the core mechanism that enables learning: gradients tell us "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "which direction and how much"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to adjust each parameter to reduce the loss."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Gradient Computation — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Gradient Computation Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Given a neural network with:\n- Inputs: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Parameters: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\theta"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (weights "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " and biases "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "b"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ")\n- Loss function: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "L(\\hat{y}, y)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (comparing prediction "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\hat{y}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to true label "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Goal"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Compute "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\theta_i}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for every parameter "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\theta_i"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The gradient "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\theta}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a vector telling us:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Direction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": which way to move "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\theta"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " to decrease loss\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Magnitude"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": how steeply the loss changes"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Gradient Computation Matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Neural networks are trained using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "gradient-based optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (typically SGD or Adam):"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\theta_{\\text{new}} = \\theta_{\\text{old}} - \\alpha \\cdot \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\theta}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\alpha"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the learning rate."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without accurate gradient computation:\n- We can't update weights properly\n- The network can't learn from data\n- Training fails completely"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Three Approaches to Gradient Computation"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Approach"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Pros"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cons"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Random search"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Try random parameter tweaks, see if loss decreases"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Simple"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inefficient, doesn't scale"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Numerical gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use finite differences: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\theta} \\approx \\frac{L(\\theta+\\epsilon) - L(\\theta)}{\\epsilon}"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Easy to implement"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slow (2 forward passes per parameter), numerically unstable"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Analytical gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use chain rule + backpropagation to compute exact derivatives"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast (1 forward + 1 backward pass), exact"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Requires manual derivation or autodiff framework"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep learning uses analytical gradients via backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because it's both efficient and exact."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Backpropagation Computes Gradients"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Backpropagation is an "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "algorithm for computing gradients of compound functions"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as a series of local, intermediate gradients."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Three-Step Process"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Identify intermediate functions (forward prop)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Build the computational graph: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x \\rightarrow \\text{layer}_1 \\rightarrow \\text{layer}_2 \\rightarrow \\dots \\rightarrow \\hat{y} \\rightarrow L"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Store all intermediate values"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compute local gradients"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- For each operation (e.g., "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\sigma(Wx)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "Wx+b"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "), compute its derivative - Examples: - Linear: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial (Wx)}{\\partial W} = x"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Activation: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial \\sigma(z)}{\\partial z} = \\sigma'(z)"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " - Loss: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial \\text{MSE}}{\\partial \\hat{y}} = 2(\\hat{y} - y)"}}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Combine with upstream error signal (chain rule)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- Multiply local gradient by "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "upstream gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (gradient from later layers) - Propagate backward: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\theta} = \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\text{upstream}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial \\text{upstream}}{\\partial \\theta}"}}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Intuition: \"Slopes Multiply\""}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The chain rule says "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "slopes multiply"}, {"type": "text", "text": " along the path from parameter to loss:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W_1} = \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\hat{y}} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial \\hat{y}}{\\partial h} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial h}{\\partial W_1}"}}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Concrete Example: 2-Layer Network"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Forward pass\nz_1 = np.dot(X, W_1)      # Linear layer 1\nh_1 = np.maximum(z_1, 0)  # ReLU activation\ny_hat = np.dot(h_1, W_2)  # Linear layer 2\nL = np.sum(y_hat**2)       # Loss (MSE)\n\n# Backward pass (gradient computation)\ndy_hat = 2.0 * y_hat                # ∂L/∂y_hat\ndW2 = h_1.T.dot(dy_hat)             # ∂L/∂W2\ndh1 = dy_hat.dot(W_2.T)             # ∂L/∂h1 (upstream gradient)\ndz1 = dh1.copy()                    # ∂L/∂z1\ndz1[z1 < 0] = 0                     # ReLU derivative: 0 where z1 < 0\ndW1 = X.T.dot(dz1)                  # ∂L/∂W1"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each line computes a gradient using the chain rule:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dy_hat"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": local gradient from loss\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dW2"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": local gradient from layer 2 × upstream gradient\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dh1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": upstream gradient passed to layer 1\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dz1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": ReLU derivative applied (local gradient)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dW1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": local gradient from layer 1 × upstream gradient"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Automatic Differentiation (Autodiff)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Modern frameworks (PyTorch, TensorFlow) use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "automatic differentiation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to compute gradients without manual derivation. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "http://d2l.ai/chapter_preliminaries/autograd.html", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "d2l"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Autograd Works"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Build computation graph"}, {"type": "text", "text": " during forward pass (tracking operations)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reverse-mode differentiation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (backprop) during backward pass"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cache intermediate values"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to avoid recomputation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# PyTorch example\nimport torch\n\nx = torch.tensor([1.0, 2.0], requires_grad=True)\nw = torch.tensor([0.5], requires_grad=True)\ny = w * x\nloss = y.sum()\n\nloss.backward()  # Autograd computes ∂loss/∂x and ∂loss/∂w\nprint(x.grad)    # Gradient w/ respect to x\nprint(w.grad)    # Gradient w/ respect to w"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Autograd engine automatically applies the chain rule through the entire graph."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Forward Mode vs. Reverse Mode Autodiff"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mode"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient computation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forward mode"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Propagate derivatives forward: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial y}{\\partial x_i}"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Few inputs, many outputs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One pass per input parameter"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reverse mode"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (backprop)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Propagate derivatives backward: "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial x_i}"}}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Many inputs, few outputs (NNs)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One pass for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all"}, {"type": "text", "text": " parameters"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Neural networks have "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "millions of weights"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (inputs) but "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "one loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (output), so "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "reverse-mode"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is essential."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient Computation Properties"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shape Rule"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When taking gradients against a scalar loss:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient at each step has the shape of the denominator"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " has same shape as "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial x}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " has same shape as "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x"}}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dimension Balancing"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For matrix operations like "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z = Wx"}}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W} = \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial z} \\cdot x^{T}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (matrix multiplication)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial x} = W^{T} \\cdot \\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial z}"}}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This ensures gradients have correct shapes for parameter updates."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of gradient computation as "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "error attribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forward"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": compute prediction and loss"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backward"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": ask \"how much did each parameter contribute to the error?\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": propagate blame backward through layers"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Update"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": adjust parameters to reduce blame (loss)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each gradient tells you: \"If I increase this weight by 1, the loss increases by "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial W}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " calculates "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\frac{\\partial L}{\\partial \\theta}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for every parameter to enable learning"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the efficient algorithm using the chain rule + dynamic programming"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Three methods"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": random search (inefficient), numerical (slow/unstable), analytical (fast/exact) → use analytical"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Autodiff frameworks"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (PyTorch/TensorFlow) automate gradient computation without manual derivation "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "link", "attrs": {"href": "http://d2l.ai/chapter_preliminaries/autograd.html", "target": "_blank", "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow", "class": "text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400", "title": null}}], "text": "d2l"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reverse-mode autodiff"}, {"type": "text", "text": " computes all gradients in one pass, essential for deep networks"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradients follow the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "shape rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": gradient has same shape as the parameter"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This is the foundation of all neural network training: without accurate gradient computation, optimization (SGD/Adam) cannot work."}]}]}}